This paper is focused on hyperparameter tuning for deep neural networks, which is a common problem in machine learning. The paper proposes a new approach to multi-fidelity Bayesian optimization, which is a popular method for optimizing black-box objectives. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision), which are also related to machine learning. Additionally, the paper mentions kernel learning, which falls under the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper proposes a method for optimizing the acquisition function, which is related to optimization and control, falling under the sub-category cs.SY (Systems and Control).
